               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DALEY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650814-name-399" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-399" type="surname" value="HINES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-399" type="given" value="JOSIAH ERASMUS"></interp>JOSIAH ERASMUS HINES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a ginger beer manufacturer, of Hoxton—on 18th May, I was in Hare-street, Woolwich, with a van of ginger beer—I left my coat in the van to go into a shop for orders, and left the van in the prisoner's possession—as I went back I saw him leaving with my coat—he got fifty feet away before I could catch him—I took him by the collar, and asked him for it—he said, "I only took it for a lark; I was going to give it back to you"—I said, "I shall take you for a lark," and gave him in custody—this (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is my coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650814-name-400" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-400" type="surname" value="JACKSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650814-name-400" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES JACKSON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, R</hi> 263). I saw the prisoner and prosecutor struggling—I was not on duty—the prosecutor gave the prisoner into my charge for stealing his coat—the prisoner said that he would make Hines pay for tearing his coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I saw the coat lying about two feet from the van, near the wheel; I thought it had dropped off some other cart, and picked it up.</p>
